criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. The patient was older than 18 years old and had not been diagnosed with diabetes
             before pregnancy. A 75-gram glucose load examination was performed during 24-28 weeks
             of gestation：GDM should be diagnosed at any time in pregnancy if one or more of the
             listed criteria are met following a 75-gram glucose load: fasting PG ≥5.1 mmol/l;
             1-hour PG ≥10.0mmol/l; 2-hour PG 8.5-11.0 mmol/l.

          2. If the patient is younger than 18 years old, consent from parents or guardians is
             required;

          3. Inclusion objects in line with the above sample sources;

          4. Signed the informed consent;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Refuse to sign the informed consent

          2. Severe mental symptoms, unable to cooperate with blood collection
